        "type": "message",
        "text": "That being said: using a dummy variable is not really a \"method\", it's just one way to parameterize a model including variation in sampling effort. If you look at a cake recipe, it will say \"add sugar\", but it usually will not specify if the sugar is to be added by spoon, by hand, or in a different way. Because at the end of the day, that does not matter :wink:",
